reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Neat cabinet, holds more than you'd expect
reviews.reviewText: I had to really think about how i was going to write this review as the FedEx delivery was a nightmare! I had ordered a different cabinet, but it was too big so i returned it and ordered this one. The tracking info said this cabinet was delivered, but when I got home, I found that FedEx delivered the first cabinet to me again, and a call to FedEx told me that they sent this cabinet back to the company of the first cabinet!!! What? After some communication with Leo with this company, he quickly sent out a replacement! Unfortunately, it arrived damaged by FedEx. After saying all that, Leo with Airiva was wonderful to work with! Not only did he send me a whole new replacement cabinet, but he also sent the part that was damaged!!! Now for the cabinet: This cabinet is small, but it holds more than it looks. It took a few hours to put together, but the instructions were easy to follow. The drawers have metal glides that move very easily. The drawers are perfect for holding rolls of wax paper, tin foil, sandwich bags etc. The only thing I don't really like is that the doors aren't deep enough to hold much more than bottles of spices. Maybe, if the dowel rods were smaller, they might hold more. The doors swing easily. You have to make sure that the back board is on straight to make sure the doors line up properly. Overall, very nice cabinet. It has kind of a funky smell, but I expect that will go away with time. Very, very good customer service from Leo with Airiva and fantastic customer service from Amazon over refund from the first cabinet that was lost!

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Turned out great!
reviews.reviewText: Great purchase since I do not have a pantry closet in my kitchen. It is a smaller cabinet but fit everything I needed perfectly and did not take up much room. Overall pretty sturdy. It does take a little time to put together, but definitely worth the buy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Well worth the cost and effort
reviews.reviewText: It took longer to assemble than suggested, but the instructions were easy to follow. When assembled it is sturdy and attractive. I use it to house my medication and supplies for my dialysis. I am very pleased with my purchase and its cost.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewText: We used this item as a pantry. I hooked up some motion sensor LED lights up on the inside with man’s do it has been great. Definately needs to be mounted to the wall when you have the shelves on the doors loaded up with stuff.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Nice cupboard, just a little smaller than anticipated.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So much better than IKEA!
reviews.reviewText: This cabinet went together beautifully. I’m used to IKEA furniture, and this experience was much better for the following reasons:1. The instructions were clear, the drawings had details, and it used words when necessary.2. There was plenty of packaging in the box to protect the boards. Everything was well labeled, even the bags of hardware.3. It came with a screwdriver! No Allen wrench in sight!3. The holes all lined up! No jamming things together!4. The cabinet was sturdy after assembly and came with cutouts on the backing for anchoring, and came with the anchoring components.The one downside I notice right off the bat is it has a noticeable chemical smell out of the box. I’m hoping it dissipates out in the open but will wipe it down with a vinegar solution if it remains.I’m very happy with my purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Wobbly and magnets don’t keep doors shut
reviews.reviewText: I don’t love it. Once it was built with everything tight, it was wobbly when moving it. Then the magnets, even screwed in all the way forward don’t keep the doors shut. I had to reinforce them just to keep them close… I didn’t even put anything heavy in the doors.It looks pretty but I wish I would’ve gotten something a bit more sturdy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars pain to put together but works
reviews.reviewText: It took us awhile to put this together and some of the part number stickers werent on. Definitely cheaply made but you get what you pay for.
